The paper focuses on developing a neural network model for converting input graphs to sequences and then decoding the target sequence. This involves natural language generation tasks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper also deals with attention-based mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning for tasks such as image recognition (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE). The paper also proposes a novel aggregation strategy, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to combine information from multiple sources. Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which are commonly reported in machine learning (cs.LG).
